questions.main_text:
_The BBC’s Journalism Trainee Scheme is the flagship journalism entry and training scheme run by the BBC Academy. Since 2007 we have recruited and trained scores of high-quality journalists, many of whom continue to work on high-profile programmes and in newsrooms across the BBC._

&NewLine;

_The scheme offers vocational journalists the opportunity to immerse themselves in BBC News for a year of high quality training and work experience. Successful applicants need to be able to demonstrate creativity, resilience in a high-pressure environment, and a thorough understanding of the role of the BBC’s journalism._

&NewLine;

Video: BBC Journalism Trainee Scheme

&NewLine;

[LINK url=http://yle.fi/plus/abitreenit/2018/kevat/EA-fi/EA-fi/attachments/index.html#q17.1|text=Avaa aineisto]

&NewLine;

You have decided to apply for the BBC Journalism Trainee Scheme. You can watch the video, if you like, to get a better idea of the scheme. To apply you are required to write either a piece of news or a text on a cultural topic (sports, theatre, fine arts, music, etc.). Write your text.

